Package org.jsweet.transpiler.util

Class Util

java.lang.Object
org.jsweet.transpiler.util.Util
public class Util extends Object
Various utilities. Static utilities (independent from JSweet context) are accessible through Util.Static.myHelper()
Author:
Renaud Pawlak, Louis Grignon

    • getRelativePath

      public String getRelativePath​(String fromPath, String toPath)
      Gets the relative path that links the two given paths. 
       assertEquals("../c", util.getRelativePath("/a/b", "/a/c"));
 assertEquals("..", util.getRelativePath("/a/b", "/a"));
 assertEquals("../e", util.getRelativePath("/a/b/c", "/a/b/e"));
 assertEquals("d", util.getRelativePath("/a/b/c", "/a/b/c/d"));
 assertEquals("d/e", util.getRelativePath("/a/b/c", "/a/b/c/d/e"));
 assertEquals("../../../d/e/f", util.getRelativePath("/a/b/c", "/d/e/f"));
 assertEquals("../..", util.getRelativePath("/a/b/c", "/a"));
 assertEquals("..", util.getRelativePath("/a/b/c", "/a/b"));

      Thanks to: http://mrpmorris.blogspot.com/2007/05/convert-absolute-path-to-relative- path.html

      Bug fix: Renaud Pawlak

      Parameters:
      fromPath - the path to start from
      toPath - the path to reach

      Gets the inheritance-based sorted class declarations.

    • getElement

      public static <T extends Element> T getElement​(standalone.com.sun.source.tree.Tree tree)
      Returns an Element corresponding to given tree (for given compilationUnit). May return an error if the tree has no corresponding element possible. For instance:
      • getElementForTree(VariableTree, ...) would likely return a VariableElement.
      • getElementForTree(NewClassTree, ...) would, on the other hand, return a TypeElement.

    • getElementNoErrors

      public static <T extends Element> T getElementNoErrors​(standalone.com.sun.source.tree.Tree tree)
      Returns an Element corresponding to given tree (for given compilationUnit). Will return null if no element matches tree. For instance:
      • getElementForTree(VariableTree, ...) would likely return a VariableElement.
      • getElementForTree(NewClassTree, ...) would, on the other hand, return a TypeElement.
